result.name: Ana Gura

reviews.text: Ambience in the restaurant was good. We were ushered quickly to a big table. Service was quite attentive and quick. Food was actually of good quality contrary to general opinion. Fish for sashimi was fresh and beautifully presented. I will commend for service and presentation. Highly recommended.

Lunch on 2019-04-21
Not bad, but not good enough.  Fish tasted fresh (4 stars).  Uni (sea urchin) was only fair (2 stars).  Service was decently good (4 stars) but food were placed on the table in a weird way.  We got a whole table to use but 2 tiny plates of appetizers were put on the side when the main dish did not come until 10 minutes later.  I had expected more for its price.  Seating was probably the weakest link.  It appeared unforgivably wrong when the operator claimed to have been in F&B industry for 13 years.  Couldn’t hang a shopping bag or any bag to the chair.  No basket provided for you to place your bags.  Seriously?  For a restaurant inside a shopping mall?  They just couldn’t care less or they expected people would be happy to put everything on the floor.  This is heartless and shall fairly tell how good a restaurant is.  Food isn’t the only thing people rate a restaurant.  Food here is not good enough anyway.  Much room for improvement.  A disappointed dining experience.

The place looks nice when you come in but the service is literally garbage. You have to wait so long and finally when your food comes it doesn’t even taste good and they made it wrong.  Once I ordered prawn sushi and asked for no wasabi.  After waiting so long it finally arrives and it had wasabi on it! Even though I said I didn’t want wasabi!  I decided to give the restaurant another chance, but they still put wasabi on it.  All in all this restaurant doesn’t even deserve the one star I had to give to write this review.

Cockroach was found on wall before dinner started. We were relocated away from the site. Waiters swiftly explained to us about the situation: it’s near the rear door. Seemed it’s not the first time it had happened.  Pricey menus.
Don’t need to hear to Andrew he is lieing

result.name: Festival Walk

reviews.text: Good arcade to shop for medium to medium-high end brands in a spacious environment with both restaurants and food court to suit varying tastes of customers. Great parking lot. Multiple sakes receipts accepted for free parking.

Very crowded and very clean like a hospital. Come here on Sunday and you can enjoy waiting for a table for an hour with everyone. Best place if you want to buy a Rolex for $900,000 to go with your yacht sitting in a port in Italy.
Multiple restaurants and shops. A very big mall, and a nice theater to watch movies. The restaurants were also very nice. A very good shopping mall overall.

I like Festival Walk as it is rarely super crowded like the malls at Sha Tin always seem to be. The TASTE supermarket is fantastic here with a range of products from around the world including Waitrose products and a good frozen section. Other stores I like here are Zara Home, Log On, M&S and the Cinema which let's you bring Starbucks in. I sometimes come here to walk around on rainy days too as it is so big and there are very few shoppers with suitcases.

I like Windows shopping here.cause if not people mountain people sea. Can very relaxed to take a look.some shop I used take a look.like hk a female designer. She design Chinese match west.she control color very. Very good. Also one best of world shoe shop. Tecstoni.name may be not correct. It is one of best Italian designer band shoe shop.
